        """Validates `tenant_id` per TPRD §15.32 (FIX — pre-authorized at
        H5-rev-3 D3 iter 2; restored after the H5-rev-2 over-correction).

        Raises:
            ValidationError: if tenant_id does not match _TENANT_ID_REGEX
                (`^[A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9_-]*$`) OR exceeds MaxTenantIDLength
                (128 chars). Go SDK has no enforcement at this layer; Python
                tightens to defeat tenant-ID-injection bugs at the SDK
                boundary (preferable to silent prefix-collision bugs).

        Implementation sketch:
            if not _TENANT_ID_REGEX.match(tenant_id):
                raise ValidationError(f"tenant_id must match {_TENANT_ID_REGEX.pattern!r}")
            if len(tenant_id) > MaxTenantIDLength:
                raise ValidationError(
                    f"tenant_id length {len(tenant_id)} exceeds MaxTenantIDLength={MaxTenantIDLength}"
                )

        Typing-only `TenantID = NewType("TenantID", str)` is permissible at
        type-check time AND the runtime check above fires regardless of
        whether the caller used the NewType wrapper.
        """
        ...
    # Mirrors KVStore methods with key prefixing.

